Class DISCARD_PAYLOAD

java.lang.Object

      org.jgroups.protocols.DISCARD_PAYLOAD

public class DISCARD_PAYLOAD
extends Protocol

Discards a message whose sequence number (in the payload, as a Long) matches seqno 2 times, before passing it down. Used for unit testing of OOB messages

Method Detail

down

public java.lang.Object down(Event evt)
Description copied from class: Protocol
An event is to be sent down the stack. The layer may want to examine its type and perform some action on it, depending on the event's type. If the event is a message MSG, then the layer may need to add a header to it (or do nothing at all) before sending it down the stack using down_prot.down(). In case of a GET_ADDRESS event (which tries to retrieve the stack's address from one of the bottom layers), the layer may need to send a new response event back up the stack using up_prot.up().
